attachments.text: Introduces “snaps” for new robust, secure app format Introduces LXD pure-container hypervisor with OpenStack Mitaka Supports IBM Z and LinuxONE systems with flat pricing Steps towards converged Ubuntu across IOT, Phone, Desktop and Server Introduces ZFS and CephFS for large-scale cloud storage LONDON 20th April 2016: Canonical announced today it will release Ubuntu 16.04 LTS [...]

text: Not suggesting we upgrade now, but I’m going to test it out on the external SSD to see how it looks for the head node.
there’s some really good shit in this distro (convergence across IoI->Server, new package format)
remains to be seen how many of the drivers and packages we need have been ported over - likely none so far
yeah probably too early to use
i figure it’ll be 6 mo before NVidia gets their major drivers moved over

have a great YT trends demo to push up, i need to do a little house keeping on the template editor how it talks, as i figured when i push a display to IS is kills my symbolic link and perms for how i was linking to the template file it was using for the editor. im going to just link to that template from the editor fed thru apache instead. then get these demos into there so we can easily switch between them using the editor for tuesday
i pulled up the editor on my tablet and it worked fine there even. so we can pretty easily use that tuesday to just switch them with my tablet while standing there
and i also noticed with the trends api that I found in our notes that there isnt a filter for country, just age and gender,  and the wires have country
on to the lighting code now that this stuff looks sweet
